have dead simple code and also super customizable, which is sometimes two conflicting ideas.

00:06:11.679 --> 00:06:16.720
So in this example, I think it's pretty dead simple. We have trial, which is a data frame,

00:06:16.799 --> 00:06:22.239
a data set, and we pass that to tblSummary from the GTSummary package, and we say I would like

00:06:22.239 --> 00:06:28.239
to have some summary statistics split by treatment, and I want to see age, grade, and response. So

00:06:28.799 --> 00:06:32.239
internally, we're looking at this. We're like, okay, well, age looks continuous. I'll default

00:06:32.239 --> 00:06:38.720
to the median IQR. Grade looks pretty categorical. I'll do that. Response, that looks dichotomous.

00:06:38.720 --> 00:06:43.440
I'm just going to give you a single line. Two of these, age and tumor response, have missing values.

00:06:43.440 --> 00:06:46.559
Let me make sure I put some information about that in the table so that you don't

00:06:47.279 --> 00:06:52.239
think that there's no missing data. And it looks again, let's start at the top, at age,

00:06:52.239 --> 00:06:57.679
and it says, okay, well, your age is like from here around to here, probably rounding to one

00:06:57.679 --> 00:07:02.720
decimal, zero decimal places to the nearest integer. It is reasonable for this variable.

