00:07:17.519 --> 00:07:24.399
Q table. That's the takeaway right here. So, and with those defaults, of course,

00:07:24.399 --> 00:07:28.720
they're all modifiable. So in this example, I'm adding the statistic argument and I'm saying,

00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:33.519
take all those continuous variables, which is in this case, just age, and rather than doing that

00:07:33.519 --> 00:07:38.079
default median IQR, I would like to see the mean and the standard deviation in parentheses next to

00:07:38.079 --> 00:07:44.239
it. So you may recognize some of this syntax. It looks just like glue, which you see in dplyr,

00:07:44.239 --> 00:07:47.600
